    <text>
        <body>
            <head>91. Telegram From the Department of State to the Embassy in <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d91fn1">Source: Carter Library,
                    National Security Affairs, Staff Material Middle East, Subject File, Box 61,
                    Libya: 2/77–12/78. Confidential; <gloss target="#t_Niact_1">Niact</gloss>
                    Immediate. Sent for information Priority to London and Rome. Printed from a copy
                    that was received in the White House Situation Room. Drafted by <persName
                        corresp="recu5YkguPqS2bb7J">Bergstrom</persName>; cleared in <gloss
                        target="#t_NEA_1">NEA</gloss>/RA, D, <gloss target="#t_NEAAFN_1"
                        >NEA/AFN</gloss>, and H; approved by <persName corresp="reciS8viNYFKOFWI7"
                        >Draper</persName>. (National Archives, RG 59, Central Foreign Policy File,
                    D780074–0628)</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1978-02-17T19:27:00+00:00">February 17, 1978, 1927Z</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>42713. Subject: Sale of U.S. Aircraft and Services to <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>.</p>
            <p>1. <orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">Dept</orgName> made following decisions
                February 16:</p>
            <p>A. To inform <orgName corresp="recmZgvBPFsMrNgrR">Lockheed</orgName> the <orgName
                    corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">Dept</orgName> will not authorize the overhaul of
                    <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>’s <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="rec1GiKVfLPrlIGzK">C–130s</rs> in the U.S.</p>
            <p>B. To turn down future <rs type="topic" corresp="rec5B6FoQIKsTYqhR">munitions
                    control</rs> license applications for the overhaul of <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>’s <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="rec1GiKVfLPrlIGzK">C–130s</rs> abroad.</p>
            <p>C. To turn down continued supply <rs type="topic" corresp="recSkg5rdjWW1fsS7">spare
                    parts</rs> and continued onsite maintenance of the aircraft.</p>
            <p>D. To inform <orgName corresp="recmZgvBPFsMrNgrR">Lockheed</orgName> the <orgName
                    corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">Dept</orgName> will recommend to <orgName
                    corresp="rec9JONpI4d5UqDCd">Commerce</orgName> approval for the export of Jet
                Star to <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>.</p>
            <p>E. To inform <orgName corresp="rec9JONpI4d5UqDCd">Commerce</orgName> that <orgName
                    corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">Dept</orgName> is not in favor of approving issuance
                of a license permitting sale of two <rs type="topic" corresp="reccFysHaUEN9EX4w"
                    >Boeing 727s</rs> to <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName>
                Arab Airlines.</p>
            <p>2. <orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">Department</orgName> understands Senator
                    <persName corresp="recEYzF12Re5k3VB7">Case</persName>’s office has learned of
                    <orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">Department</orgName>’s decision and plans
                make public announcement at 1500 hours Washington time. <orgName
                    corresp="recmZgvBPFsMrNgrR">Lockheed</orgName> concerned about safety its
                personnel in <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> and unable to
                contact Team Chief West. Please inform West of impending announcement, as well as
                heads of other American companies, if you believe <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> reaction might be violent and
                Americans should be cautioned. In meanwhile, <orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl"
                    >Department</orgName> attempting to persuade <persName
                    corresp="recEYzF12Re5k3VB7">Case</persName>’s office to delay press
                announcement.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>
                    <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">
                        <hi rendition="simple_bold">Vance</hi>
                    </persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
